xul-ext-icedove-conversations (2.8.1-1nano) unstable; urgency=low

  * New upstream release
     * New features
     - The address for replying can now be changed in the quick reply.
     - The "quick reply" feature now uses an HTML editor (#369), meaning
       that no loss of formatting occurs when replying. The message will
       be sent as HTML only if necessary (just like the regular composition
       process). This fixes several other issues related to signatures
       (#353, #644, #779). The hidden, unsupported compose-in-a-tab feature
       provided by this addon hence also uses HTML composition.
    - New "open" action for attachments added to a quick-reply.
    - The "open messages in: a new window" preference (in Advanced >
      Reading and Display) is now honored. This means that you can open a
      conversation in a separate window by flipping this preference and
      double-clicking on a message in the thread pane, or hitting the
      "pop out" button in the conversation toolbar.
    - Support for the DKIM verifier addon.
    - Option to always collapse signatures.
    * Bugfixes.
    - Fix the Lightning plugin support.
    - Contact tooltips now display properly even when the message is collapsed.
    - The addon no longer waits for images to load before reflowing and
      adjusting the height of a message.
    - Several other bugfixes related to changes in Thunderbird.

 -- Christopher Roy Bratusek <nano@jpberlin.de>  Mon, 11 Aug 2014 18:29:30 +0200

